+# Pelorus Development Journal
+
+Active investigation logs, decisions, and their reasoning.
+
+## Seeding / Bootstrapping Prometheus
+
+**Start date:** 2026-06-05
+
+**Goal:** Seed 6 months of historical DORA metrics for 4 fictional teams across the demo.
+
+**Problem:** Seed script generated 540 metrics with timestamps spanning 150 days, but all appeared as "NOW" in Grafana.
+
+**Timeline of fixes:**
+
+### Fix 1: Prometheus Pod Restart Loop
+- **Symptom:** Prometheus pod constantly restarting
+- **Cause:** Helm template used `randAlphaNum 32` for OAuth cookie secret → new value on every reconciliation
+- **Fix:** Generate cookie secret once, persist in Kubernetes Secret
+- **Files:** `pelorus-operator/helm-charts/pelorus/templates/prometheus-oauth-cookie-secret.yaml`
+
+### Fix 2: Webhook Timestamps Not Passing Through
+- **Symptom:** Webhook exporter had correct timestamps but Prometheus used scrape time
+- **Cause:** Explicit timestamps not being passed as sample timestamps in Prometheus metrics format
+- **Fix:** Modified `in_memory_metric.py` to pass timestamp as explicit sample timestamp
+- **Files:** `exporters/webhook/store/in_memory_metric.py`
+
+### Fix 3: ServiceMonitor Ignoring Timestamps
+- **Symptom:** Prometheus ignored explicit timestamps from webhook exporter
+- **Cause:** ServiceMonitor had `honorTimestamps: false`
+- **Fix:** Changed to `honorTimestamps: true`
+- **Files:** `pelorus-operator/helm-charts/pelorus/charts/exporters/templates/servicemonitor.yaml`
+
+### Fix 4: Scrape Model Rejection → Switch to Backfill
+- **Problem:** Prometheus scrape model rejects samples "too old or too far into the future"
+- **Solution:** Switched from webhook POSTing to **Prometheus backfill** (offline TSDB block creation)
+- **Files:** `demo/seed-metrics.sh` (complete refactor)
+
+### Fix 5: Out-of-Order Ingestion Disabled
+- **Symptom:** Backfill blocks created successfully but data not queryable in historical time ranges
+- **Root cause:** `outofordertimewindow: 0` — OOO completely disabled
+- **Fix:** Enable OOO with `180d` window
+- **Files:** `demo/install.sh` sets `prometheus_out_of_order_time_window: 180d`
+
+### Fix 6: Prometheus Operator Too Old
+- **Symptom:** OOO configuration not being applied despite correct template
+- **Root cause:** Prometheus Operator v0.56.3 (2022) doesn't support `additionalArgs` field in Prometheus CRD
+- **Fix:** Install v0.70.0+ from k8s-operatorhub catalog instead of OCP community-operators
+- **Files:** `demo/install.sh` now verifies operator version, uses operatorhubio-catalog
+
+### Fix 7: OpenShift SCC Conflict
+- **Symptom:** Prometheus Operator pod fails with SCC error
+- **Cause:** k8s-operatorhub CSV hardcodes `runAsUser: 65534`, conflicts with OCP namespace UID ranges `[1000730000, 1000739999]`
+- **Fix:** `demo/install.sh` patches CSV to remove hardcoded `runAsUser`, OCP assigns from namespace range
+- **Note:** Patch may need reapplied on operator upgrade via OLM
+
+**Current status:** All 7 fixes applied and verified. Seed script generates 6 months of historical data (Nov 2025 → Apr 2026) that's queryable in Grafana.
+
+**What was learned:**
+- Remote Write API doesn't solve OOO — same limitation
+- Auto-compaction wasn't the problem; OOO being disabled was
+- Backfill is the correct tool for bulk historical ingestion
+- Persistent storage is required for backfill to survive restarts
+
+## Open Tasks
+
+### Upstream OCP Catalog PR
+- **Problem:** OCP community-operators has Prometheus Operator v0.56.3 (May 2022)
+- **Target:** Get v0.70.0+ into OCP catalog with SCC compatibility
+- **Reference:** `demo/ADD_OPERATORHUBIO_CATALOG.md`
+- **Decision needed:** Once done, remove temporary catalog source AND CSV patch from `demo/install.sh`
+
+### Automate CSV Patch
+- **Current:** Patch applies automatically in fresh installs via `demo/install.sh`
+- **TODO:** Make patch idempotent, handle upgrades, document that it may need reapplication after OLM upgrades
+
