+# Pelorus Troubleshooting
+
+Operational runbooks for common failures.
+
+---
+
+## Prometheus Pod Restarting
+
+**Symptom:** Prometheus pod constantly restarting
+
+**Cause:** OAuth cookie secret generated with `randAlphaNum 32` → new value on every reconciliation → pod deletion and recreation
+
+**Solution:**
+
+```bash
+# Verify the secret exists
+oc get secret prometheus-oauth-cookie -n pelorus
+
+# If missing, re-run install or create manually
+oc apply -n pelorus -f - <<EOF
+apiVersion: v1
+kind: Secret
+metadata:
+  name: prometheus-oauth-cookie
+  namespace: pelorus
+type: Opaque
+data:
+  cookie-secret: <base64-encoded-value>
+EOF
+
+# Restart Prometheus to pick up the secret
+oc rollout restart statefulset prometheus-prometheus-pelorus -n pelorus
+```
+
+**Prevention:** Always set `prometheus_oauth_cookie_secret` in the Pelorus CR spec.
+
+---
+
+## Historical Backfill Data Not Queryable
+
+**Symptom:** Seed script completes, TSDB blocks created, but queries return no data for historical time ranges.
+
+**Cause:** Out-of-order ingestion disabled (`outofordertimewindow: 0`) or Prometheus Operator too old.
+
+**Solution:**
+
+```bash
+# 1. Check Prometheus Operator version
+oc get csv -n pelorus | grep prometheus
+# Need v0.59.0 or higher
+
+# 2. Verify OOO configuration applied
+oc get prometheus prometheus-pelorus -n pelorus -o yaml | grep -A 3 additionalArgs
+# Should show: storage.tsdb.out-of-order-time-window: "180d"
+
+# 3. Verify Prometheus container args
+oc get pod prometheus-prometheus-pelorus-0 -n pelorus \
+  -o jsonpath='{.spec.containers[?(@.name=="prometheus")].args}' | grep out-of-order
+# Should include: --storage.tsdb.out-of-order-time-window=180d
+
+# 4. Query Prometheus config
+oc port-forward -n pelorus svc/prometheus-pelorus 9090:9091
+curl http://localhost:9090/api/v1/status/config | jq '.data.yaml' | grep outofordertimewindow
+# Should output: outofordertimewindow: 180d (NOT 0)
+```
+
+**Fix:** If operator is too old:
+
+```bash
+# Delete old operator subscription
+oc delete subscription prometheus -n pelorus
+oc delete csv -n pelorus -l operators.coreos.com/prometheus.pelorus
+
+# Re-run install (installs v0.70.0+ from k8s-operatorhub)
+./demo/install.sh
+```
+
+---
+
+## Metrics Showing Wrong Timestamps (Real-Time Scraping)
+
+**Symptom:** Webhook events have correct timestamps but Grafana shows them as "NOW"
+
+**Checklist:**
+
+```bash
+# 1. Verify honorTimestamps is enabled
+oc get servicemonitor -n pelorus -o yaml | grep honorTimestamps
+# Should show: honorTimestamps: true
+
+# 2. Check webhook exporter metrics endpoint
+oc port-forward -n pelorus svc/webhook-exporter 18080:8080
+# Visit http://localhost:18080/metrics and look for explicit timestamps in output
+
+# 3. Verify in_memory_metric.py passes timestamps
+# Check exporters/webhook/store/in_memory_metric.py for explicit sample timestamp handling
+```
+
+---
+
+## Backfill Corruption Errors
+
+**Symptom:** `promtool tsdb create-blocks-from` fails with corruption or permission errors
+
+**Solution:**
+
+```bash
+# Clean up partial blocks
+oc exec -n pelorus prometheus-prometheus-pelorus-0 -c prometheus -- \
+  rm -rf /prometheus/01KRM*
+
+# Ensure /prometheus is writable (PVC mounted)
+oc exec -n pelorus prometheus-prometheus-pelorus-0 -c prometheus -- \
+  ls -la /prometheus/
+
+# Verify TMPDIR is set for promtool
+oc exec -n pelorus prometheus-prometheus-pelorus-0 -c prometheus -- \
+  env | grep TMPDIR
+```
+
+---
+
+## PVC Not Binding
+
+**Symptom:** Prometheus pod stuck in Pending or CrashLoopBackOff with PVC errors
+
+**Solution:**
+
+```bash
+# Check available storage classes
+oc get storageclass
+
+# CRC uses: crc-csi-hostpath-provisioner
+# AWS uses: gp2 or gp3
+# Azure uses: managed-premium
+
+# Update the value in your deployment
+helm install pelorus pelorus-operator/helm-charts/pelorus -n pelorus \
+  --set prometheus_storage=true \
+  --set prometheus_storage_pvc_storageclass=crc-csi-hostpath-provisioner
+```
+
+---
+
+## Prometheus Operator Fails with SCC Error
+
+**Symptom:** Operator pod fails to create with:
+
+```
+unable to validate against any security context constraint:
+provider restricted-v2: .containers[0].runAsUser: Invalid value: 65534:
+must be in the ranges: [1000730000, 1000739999]
+```
+
+**Cause:** k8s-operatorhub CSV hardcodes `runAsUser: 65534`, conflicts with OpenShift namespace UID ranges.
+
+**Solution:**
+
+```bash
+# Get the CSV name
+CSV_NAME=$(oc get csv -n pelorus | grep prometheusoperator | awk '{print $1}')
+
+# Patch to remove runAsUser
+oc patch csv $CSV_NAME -n pelorus --type=json \
+  -p='[{"op": "remove", "path": "/spec/install/spec/deployments/0/spec/template/spec/securityContext/runAsUser"}]'
+
+# Delete deployment to trigger recreation
+oc delete deployment prometheus-operator -n pelorus
+
+# Verify operator starts
+oc get pods -n pelorus -l app.kubernetes.io/name=prometheus-operator
+```
+
+**Verification:** Check operator runs with OpenShift-assigned UID:
+
+```bash
+oc get pod -n pelorus -l app.kubernetes.io/name=prometheus-operator \
+  -o jsonpath='{.spec.securityContext.runAsUser}'
+# Should output a UID in the namespace range (e.g., 1000730000)
+```
+
+---
+
+## Common Diagnostic Commands
+
+```bash
+# Check Pelorus CR status
+oc get pelorus -n pelorus -o yaml
+
+# Check all operators in namespace
+oc get pods -n pelorus -o wide
+
+# Check operator logs
+oc logs -n pelorus-operator-system deployment/pelorus-operator-controller-manager -f
+
+# Check Prometheus data directory
+oc exec -n pelorus prometheus-prometheus-pelorus-0 -c prometheus -- \
+  ls -la /prometheus/
+
+# Query Prometheus for deploy metrics
+oc exec -n pelorus prometheus-prometheus-pelorus-0 -c prometheus -- \
+  promtool query instant http://localhost:9090 'count(deploy_timestamp)'
+
+# Check Grafana dashboards
+oc port-forward -n pelorus svc/grafana 3000:3000
+# Visit http://localhost:3000, check "DORA Metrics" dashboard
+```
